==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indefectible
<hw>In`de*fect"i*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>defectible</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>ind⟦eacute⟧fectible</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not defectible; unfailing;
not liable to defect, failure, or decay.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An <qex>indefectible</qex> treasure in the heavens.</q>
<rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A state of <qex>indefectible</qex> virtue and happiness.</q>
<rj><qau>S. Clarke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indefective</ent>⟦br⟧
